>Description:
In the editor, when I double click in a word it should select the word up to the next/previous dash (or whitespace), not the whole word. A triple click should select the whole name. This follows from the practice of using dashes to separate the words that make up a name.
>How-To-Repeat:
Make a name composed of multiple words separeated by dashes. Double click on one of the words, the whole name is selected rather than just the word.
>Fix:
>Audit-Trail:
