 --089e01537580ca758e04e32d29ef
 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
 
 What is the authority you cite for these design decisions?
 
 I'm not finding anything about either of these specifically in the apple
 human interface guidelines, but Apple's TextEdit app treats triple click as
 selecting a whole line, not a word.
 
 As for the behavior of hyphens, what you ask for matches TextEdit, but in
 Racket programs, most of the time hyphens are inside "words" (really:
 symbols) and this is why we have the behavior we have. It has been this way
 for more than a decade in DrRacket, I believe, and so it seems like a bad
 idea to change, as I expect many people are used to the current behavior.
 
 Robby
 
 
 
