Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/13947: A double click on a name should stop
 at a dash
Date: Fri, 09 Aug 2013 07:09:09 -0700

 I didn't refer to any authority, I was suggesting a change (I marked it 
 as such,
 not a bug) that would make the editor easier to use.
 
 In TextEdit the word separator is space and it has the double click 
 behavior I suggest.
 Racket is a special purpose computer language editing tool and could 
 reasonably
 have slightly different behavior. The names in Racket are very often 
 words separated
 by hyphens, so it makes perfect sense (to me) to mimic the behavior of 
 TextEdit, but
 with hyphen taking the place of space. I like programming editors that 
 are syntax
 aware and make your life easier.
 
 Try out Emacs (on the Mac, or PC/Linux) on Lisp code and the mouse works 
 the way I suggest.
 
 You are right though that even in Emacs the triple click selects a whole 
 line.
 
 -- Doug
 
