 --047d7b47249c36819304e396947b
 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
 
 I see. Thank you for clarifying that this was a request. I misunderstood
 your original message.
 
 I found this (old) copy of the human interface guidelines that suggests
 that DrRacket's current behavior is the right one:
 
 http://dropbox.scripting.com/dave/misc/appleHumanInterfaceGuidelines.pdf
 
 with the possible exception that hyphen should be considered a word
 separator. Indeed, some 10 or 15 years ago, I believe DrRacket did that,
 but I found that making hyphen as a non-separator worked better, since I
 usually wanted to get an entire identifier when I double click on it (as an
 identifier is more logically a "word" in a Racket program, IMO). So it has
 been that way for a long time and I don't think we should change it now, as
 many people are, I presume, used to this behavior.
 
 Meanwhile, you can control how double-clicking works by making your
 keybindings file. Below is one that does what you want, I believe. (I've
 put more code than is strictly necessary, so you can maybe make other
 tweaks.)
 
 hth,
 Robby
 
 
 #lang s-exp framework/keybinding-lang
 
 (define map (make-object editor-wordbreak-map%))
 
 (send map set-map  #\< '(line selection))  ; interfaces e.g.the canvas<%>
 interface
 (send map set-map  #\> '(line selection))  ; interfaces, casts e.g.
 string->path
 (send map set-map  #\% '(line selection))  ; intefraces, classes
 (send map set-map  #\? '(line selection))  ; predicates
 (send map set-map  #\' '(line selection))  ; literal symbols
 (send map set-map  #\! '(line selection))  ; assignments e.g. set
 ;(send map set-map  #\- '(line selection))  ; hyphens
 (send map set-map  #\: '(line selection)); valid identifiers with colons
 
 (define (select-a-non-hypen-word text event)
   (when (and (is-a? event mouse-event%)
              (send event button-down?)
              (is-a? text text%))
     (define x-box (box (send event get-x)))
     (define y-box (box (send event get-y)))
     (define eol-box (box #f))
     (send text global-to-local x-box y-box)
     (define click-pos (send text find-position
                             (unbox x-box)
                             (unbox y-box)
                             eol-box))
     (define start-pos (send text get-start-position))
     (define end-pos (send text get-end-position))
     (define eol (unbox eol-box))
     (define start-box (box click-pos))
     (define end-box (box click-pos))
     (define orig-map (send text get-wordbreak-map))
     (send text set-wordbreak-map map)
     (send text find-wordbreak
           start-box
           end-box
           'selection)
     (send text set-wordbreak-map orig-map)
     (send text set-position
           (unbox start-box)
           (unbox end-box))))
 
 
 (keybinding "leftbuttondouble" select-a-non-hypen-word)
 
 
 
 
