 <br>
 In TextEdit the word separator is space and it has the double click behavio=
 r I suggest.<br>
 Racket is a special purpose computer language editing tool and could reason=
 ably<br>
 have slightly different behavior. The names in Racket are very often words =
 separated<br>
 by hyphens, so it makes perfect sense (to me) to mimic the behavior of Text=
 Edit, but<br>
 with hyphen taking the place of space. I like programming editors that are =
 syntax<br>
 aware and make your life easier.<br>
