 <br>
 *** Description:<br>
 In the editor, when I double click in a word it should select the word up<b=
 r>
 to the next/previous dash (or whitespace), not the whole word. A triple<br>
 click should select the whole name. This follows from the practice of using=
 <br>
 dashes to separate the words that make up a name.<br>
 <br>
 *** How to repeat:<br>
 Make a name composed of multiple words separeated by dashes. Double click<b=
 r>
 on one of the words, the whole name is selected rather than just the word.<=
 br>
