 Earlier today, Robby Findler wrote:
 > They work on something approximating identifiers, not (English)
 > words or sexps (or actual identifier syntax for that matter).
 
 I intentionally used "sexpr" rather than "a non-list
 sexpr-estimation", since double-clicking also selects list sexprs when
 use on a paren -- so as far as the usage goes, it is (an approximation
 of) sexpr selection...
 
 
 > But they should all be consistent, at least in the keybindings
 > dialog.
 
 I did look at the list of keybindings and didn't see the double clicks
 there -- are they included?  In any case, I was referring to the use
 of "word" in function names.
 
